main event: On August 4, 1966, a civilian witnessed one to three unidentified flying objects in Holly, Michigan, observing them for approximately 15-20 minutes.
interesting points: The objects appeared to be flashing lights above the horizon,The witness noted that one object was about the size of a star and pulsating in brightness,The sighting occurred at a low altitude and was headed westward,Multiple voices indicated that the object was making sounds or communicating,The witness expressed uncertainty about the true nature of the objects after speaking with friends about their observations.
sighted object: one to three unidentified flying objects
witness description: A civilian who reported their sighting directly to Project Blue Book.
